    • signIn

      @PostMapping("/sign-in") public java.lang.String signIn​(@Validated(addNewUser.class) @ModelAttribute("user") Userr user, org.springframework.validation.BindingResult result, org.springframework.ui.Model model)
      Post request receiver for Sign-in register.
      Parameters:
      user - : User object previously passed empty, expected to bring information given by the user.
      result - : Object that validates the fields with the information given by the user.
      model - : Model from which the User object is obtained.
      Returns:
      Login template to render : if there is no error on the data given by the user. Sign-in template : if there are error's on the data given by the user.

    • showUsers

      @PreAuthorize("hasRole(\'Administrador\')") @GetMapping("/users/") public java.lang.String showUsers​(org.springframework.ui.Model model)
      This route show all the users with "Regular" role, registered on the system, can only be accessed by the "Administrador" role user.
      Parameters:
      model - .
      Returns:
      Template to be rendered with the information of all "Regular" role users if the user who called it has "Administrador" role. Access denied template otherwise.

    • pwdChangePost

      @PostMapping("/pwd-change/") public java.lang.String pwdChangePost​(@Validated(addNewUser.class) @ModelAttribute("user") Userr user, org.springframework.validation.BindingResult result, org.springframework.ui.Model model, @RequestParam(value="action",required=true) java.lang.String action)

      result - : Object that validates the password given by the user.

      action - : Action that the user want to perform when on the template.
